%N A397231 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} (-1)^(k+1) * AH(2*k,3)/k, where AH(k,3) = A136675(k)/A334582(k) is the k-th alternating harmonic (or skew-harmonic) number of order 3.
%H A397231 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-21262-8">More (Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer Cham, 2023. See section 4.22, p. 426.
%H A397231 <a href="/index/Ha#harmonic">Index entries for sequences related to harmonic numbers</a>.
%F A397231 Equals 3*log(2)*zeta(3)/32 + 161*zeta(4)/128 - G^2, where G is Catalan's constant (A006752).
%e A397231 0.600479443307523754085187355435477061459458005619328...
